{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.4",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 4 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:1",
      "text": "Listen, sons, to a father’s instruction. Pay attention and know understanding;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:2",
      "text": "for I give you sound learning. Don’t forsake my law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:3",
      "text": "For I was a son to my father, tender and an only child in the sight of my mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:4",
      "text": "He taught me, and said to me: “Let your heart retain my words. Keep my commandments, and live.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:5",
      "text": "Get wisdom. Get understanding. Don’t forget, and don’t deviate from the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:6",
      "text": "Don’t forsake her, and she will preserve you. Love her, and she will keep you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:7",
      "text": "Wisdom is supreme. Get wisdom. Yes, though it costs all your possessions, get understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:8",
      "text": "Esteem her, and she will exalt you. She will bring you to honor when you embrace her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:9",
      "text": "She will give to your head a garland of grace. She will deliver a crown of splendor to you.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:10",
      "text": "Listen, my son, and receive my sayings. The years of your life will be many.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:11",
      "text": "I have taught you in the way of wisdom. I have led you in straight paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:12",
      "text": "When you go, your steps will not be hampered. When you run, you will not stumble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:13",
      "text": "Take firm hold of instruction. Don’t let her go. Keep her, for she is your life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:14",
      "text": "Don’t enter into the path of the wicked. Don’t walk in the way of evil men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:15",
      "text": "Avoid it, and don’t pass by it. Turn from it, and pass on.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:16",
      "text": "For they don’t sleep unless they do evil. Their sleep is taken away, unless they make someone fall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:17",
      "text": "For they eat the bread of wickedness and drink the wine of violence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:18",
      "text": "But the path of the righteous is like the dawning light that shines more and more until the perfect day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:19",
      "text": "The way of the wicked is like darkness. They don’t know what they stumble over.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:20",
      "text": "My son, attend to my words. Turn your ear to my sayings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:21",
      "text": "Let them not depart from your eyes. Keep them in the center of your heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:22",
      "text": "For they are life to those who find them, and health to their whole body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:23",
      "text": "Keep your heart with all diligence, for out of it is the wellspring of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:24",
      "text": "Put away from yourself a perverse mouth. Put corrupt lips far from you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:25",
      "text": "Let your eyes look straight ahead. Fix your gaze directly before you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:26",
      "text": "Make the path of your feet level. Let all of your ways be established.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.4.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:27",
      "text": "Don’t turn to the right hand nor to the left. Remove your foot from evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
